<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 4:26PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Beaver
County through 500 PM CDT...
At 426 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Beaver, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Forgan and Mocane.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
